chunk_text: [case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=DIAGNOSIS] Poorly differentiated carcinoma. Primary site is unknown. Morphologic features are suggestive of a non-small cell carcinoma.
[case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=LYMPH_NODES] Six lymph nodes examined. All lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma (0/6).
[case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=MARGINS] Resection margins are uninvolved by invasive carcinoma. Closest margin measures 18 mm.
[case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=DIAGNOSIS] Tumor size measures 4.0 cm in greatest dimension. No vascular or pleural invasion identified.
[case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=IHC] Immunohistochemistry shows tumor cells positive for CK7 and TTF-1. Tumor cells are negative for CK20 and p53.
[case_id=INPUT_00001 | section=DIAGNOSIS] Pathologic staging information: pT2N0. No evidence of distant metastasis identified.
